newsitem.title: USA: Parker & Parsley discovers oil in W.Texas.
newsitem.headline: Parker & Parsley discovers oil in W.Texas.

text.p: Parker & Parsley Petroleum Co said on Friday it made a new oil discovery in the War-Wink West field arena in West Texas which tested at rates up to 720 barrels of oil per day.
The well, in the Delaware Basin of West Texas, was now producing at its expected allowable 350 barrels of oil per day and 374 cubic feet of gas per day, the company said.
Parker & Parsley and Enserch Exploration Inc each own a 50 percent working interest in the well, Parker said.
Production tests were conducted over a gross interval of about 150 feet, the company said.
